President Trump held a ceremony at the White House to unveil the Roadmap to Empower Veterans and End the National Tragedy of Suicide. The initiative aims to address the urgent struggle of veteran suicide and provide support for veterans. The President highlighted the actions his administration has taken to support veterans, including the approval of Veterans Choice, the signing of the VA Accountability Act, and securing record funding for the VA. He also emphasized the need for bold action to end the tragedy of veteran suicide, stating that 20 veterans and service members take their own lives every day. The President announced the launch of a national public awareness campaign and a national research strategy to evaluate effective treatments for mental health issues faced by veterans. Secretary of Veterans Affairs Robert Wilkie and Second Lady Karen Pence also spoke at the event, expressing their gratitude for the President's leadership on this issue.